      <para id="id1171903213646">The accent normally falls on the first beat – <emphasis effect="bold">1</emphasis> 2 3 4</para>
      <para id="id1171896894363">STEP 7: </para>
      <para id="id1171895255964">Analyse the form of the song by following the given score:</para>
      <list id="id1171905876748" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>The song consists of 32 bars: A (8 bars) + A (8 bars) + B (8 bars) + A (8 bars).</item>
        <item>These 32 bars can be called the Theme or Chorus (Jazz term).</item>
        <item>To develop the song into a Theme and Variation form, the following can serve as an  example:</item>
      </list>
      <list id="id1171904849129" list-type="bulleted">
        <item><emphasis effect="italics">Chorus 1</emphasis> = Theme  Whole class sings the original version</item>
        <item><emphasis effect="italics">Chorus 2</emphasis> – Variation 1 Group 1 </item>
        <item><emphasis effect="italics">Chorus 3</emphasis> – Variation 2 Group 2</item>
        <item><emphasis effect="italics">Chorus 4</emphasis> – Variation 3 Group 3, etc.</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1171897679772"><emphasis effect="bold">IMPORTANT:</emphasis> The tempo and basic beat must be kept throughout!</para>
      <para id="id1171905838342">STEP 8: </para>
      <para id="id1171895295628">Listen to the recording by <emphasis effect="bold">Abdullah Ibrahim</emphasis> (Dollar Brand) and discuss the following statement. (The educator will provide the background information.)</para>
